1 (a) Creation. There is created the Unemployment Compensation Benefit
2 Modernization Advisory Committee to advise the Department of Labor on the
3 implementation and deployment of technological upgrades to the delivery
4 system for unemployment compensation benefits.
5 (b) Membership. The Committee shall be composed of the following
6 members:
7 (1) two current members of the House of Representatives, not all from
8 the same political party, appointed by the Speaker of the House, of whom one
9 shall be a member of the Joint Information Technology Oversight Committee
10 and one shall be a member of the House Committee on Commerce and
11 Economic Development;
12 (2) two current members of the Senate, not all from the same political
13 party, appointed by the Committee on Committees, of whom one shall be a
14 member of the Joint Information Technology Oversight Committee and one
15 shall be a member of the Senate Committee on Economic Development,
16 Housing and General Affairs;
17 (3) three employees of the Department of Labor who will regularly use
18 the technological upgrades, who shall be appointed by the Commissioner of
19 Labor;
20 (4) one employee from the Agency of Digital Services, who shall be
21 appointed by the Secretary of Digital Services;
