1 (5) one representative of organized labor associated with the
2 construction trades, who shall be nominated by a State labor federation and
3 appointed by the Governor;
4 (6) one representative of a group representing employers, who shall be
5 appointed by the Governor; and
6 (7) one attorney experienced in representing unemployment insurance
7 claimants, who shall be appointed by the Director of Vermont Legal Aid.
8 (c) Powers and duties. The Committee shall study the technological
9 upgrades to the delivery system for unemployment compensation benefits and
10 shall have the following powers and duties:
11 (1) to monitor the implementation and deployment of the upgrades;
12 (2) to be able to request information related to the upgrades at any time;
13 (3) to make recommendations to the Department of Labor at any time;
14 and
15 (4) to provide assistance on testing the upgrades.
16 (d) Assistance. The Committee shall have the administrative and technical
17 assistance of the Department of Labor, including for the purpose of scheduling
18 meetings.
19 (e) Report. The Committee shall submit a written report to the Joint
20 Information Technology Oversight Committee, the House Committee on
21 Commerce and Economic Development, and the Senate Committee on
