1 Economic Development, Housing and General Affairs on a quarterly basis,
2 with the first report due on or before September 30, 2025. The report shall
3 include the Committee’s assessment of the progress regarding implementation
4 and testing of the technological upgrades, a list of recommendations that the
5 Committee has made to the Department of Labor, and whether the Department
6 of Labor has accepted those recommendations. The Committee shall provide
7 the Department of Labor with a draft copy of the report at least 30 days prior to
8 its submission, and the Department of Labor shall be permitted to have its
9 response included in the quarterly report.
10 (f) Meetings.
11 (1) The Commissioner of Labor, or the Commissioner’s designee, shall
12 call the first meeting of the Committee to occur on or before May 1, 2025.
13 (2) The Committee shall meet at least once every two months.
14 (3) The Committee shall select a chair from among its members at the
15 first meeting.
16 (4) A majority of the membership shall constitute a quorum.
17 (5) The Committee shall cease to exist on June 30, 2026 or whenever
18 the Committee determines by a two-thirds vote that the technological upgrades
19 have been successfully implemented, whichever is later.
20 (g) Compensation and reimbursement.
